The paper deals with the design of an iterative receiver that incorporates sparse channel estimation. This topic falls under the area of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also uses a unifying framework of combined belief-propagation and mean-field, which is commonly used in statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the receiver in terms of mean-squared error and bit error rate, which are metrics commonly used in multimedia systems (cs.MM).
